Message.MsgText: UNINSTALL_CONNECTION_FACTORY_NOT_FOUND_CWSJO0028=CWSJO0028W: Cannot find CMP connection factory {0}.
Message.Explanation: The CMP connection factory created by the installer was not found.
Message.UserResponse: Locate the repository's CMP connection factory and manually remove it.

Message.MsgText: INSTALL_MULTIPLE_SERVERS_CWSJO0017=CWSJO0017E: A server is not specified but more than one server was found. There are {0} servers on node {1}.
Message.Explanation: There is more than one server configured for the node, and the command does not know which server to use.
Message.UserResponse: Run the script specifying the names of a node and server.

Message.MsgText: UNABLE_TO_CREATE_REPOSITORY_CWSJO0010=CWSJO0010E: An SDO repository instance cannot be created: exception {0}.
Message.Explanation: An SDO repository instance cannot be created because the sib.sdoConfig.jar file is missing or corrupted.
Message.UserResponse: If the problem persists, additional information might be available if you search for the message ID on the following Web sites: WebSphere Application Server Support page: http://www.ibm.com/software/webservers/appserv/was/support/ WebSphere Application Server for z/OS Support page: http://www.ibm.com/software/webservers/appserv/zos_os390/support/ .

Message.MsgText: UNINSTALL_CONNECTION_FACTORY_REMOVED_CWSJO0027=CWSJO0027I: Successfully removed CMP connection factory {0}.
Message.Explanation: The uninstaller has removed the connection factory used by the repository's data source.
Message.UserResponse: No action is required.

Message.MsgText: CANNOT_REGISTER_EMPTY_VALUE_CWSJO0002=CWSJO0002E: The SDO repository cannot store an empty array value.
Message.Explanation: An attempt was made to register an empty byte array value in the repository.
Message.UserResponse: Ensure all calls to store data in the repository specify a non-empty byte array as the value.

Message.MsgText: NAME_TOO_LONG_CWSJO0045=CWSJO0045E: The name for the resource is too long for the system. The maximum permitted length of a name is {0} characters. The provided name was "{1}".
Message.Explanation: An attempt was made to register a resource with a name that is longer than the underlying database allows.
Message.UserResponse: Use a shorter name when registering the resource.

Message.MsgText: INSTALL_MULTIPLE_NODES_CWSJO0039=CWSJO0039E: Node not specified for multiple node cell. There are {0} nodes in the cell.
Message.Explanation: There is more than one node configured for the cell.
Message.UserResponse: Run the script specifying the names of a node and server.

Message.MsgText: INSTALL_WRITING_DDL_CWSJO0041=CWSJO0041I: Creating DDL file {0}.
Message.Explanation: The installer is creating the DDL file for the Derby database.
Message.UserResponse: No action is required.

Message.MsgText: UNINSTALL_COMPLETE_CWSJO0030=CWSJO0030I: SDO repository uninstallation complete.
Message.Explanation: The uninstaller has completed.
Message.UserResponse: No action is required.

Message.MsgText: INSTALL_DATA_SOURCE_ALREADY_EXISTS_CWSJO0013=CWSJO0013E: Data source {0} already exists.
Message.Explanation: The installer cannot continue because the data source it will create already exists.
Message.UserResponse: If the SDO repository is already installed, do not install it again. Otherwise manually install the SDO repository to avoid naming conflicts with the existing configuration.

Message.MsgText: CANNOT_REGISTER_NULL_VALUE_CWSJO0003=CWSJO0003E: The SDO repository cannot store null values.
Message.Explanation: An attempt was made to register a null value in the repository.
Message.UserResponse: Ensure all calls to store data in the repository specify non-null values.

Message.MsgText: UNINSTALL_UNINSTALLING_EJB_APP_CWSJO0029=CWSJO0029I: Uninstalling application {0}.
Message.Explanation: The uninstaller is uninstalling the application component of the SDO repository.
Message.UserResponse: No action is required.

Message.MsgText: NAME_ALREADY_USED_CWSJO0004=CWSJO0004E: A name is already in use: {0}.
Message.Explanation: An attempt was made to register a value using a name already used in the repository.
Message.UserResponse: Use a different name, or delete the existing value for the name, or specify "overwrite" when writing to the repository.

Message.MsgText: MBEAN_REMOVE_CWSJO0035=CWSJO0035I: Resource {0} removed.
Message.Explanation: The resource has been removed from the repository.
Message.UserResponse: No action is required.

Message.MsgText: INSTALL_USAGE_CWSJO0024=CWSJO0024E: Incorrect parameters given. Usage: {0}
Message.Explanation: The script was called with an incorrect set of parameters.
Message.UserResponse: Call the script again using the parameters as described in the message.

Message.MsgText: INSTALL_CONFIGURING_DATA_SOURCE_CWSJO0019=CWSJO0019I: Configuring data source {0}.
Message.Explanation: The installer is creating the data source configuration object.
Message.UserResponse: No action is required.

Message.MsgText: MBEAN_IMPORT_FAIL_CWSJO0034=CWSJO0034E: Error importing resource {0} from file {1}: {2}
Message.Explanation: The resource cannot be imported from the file. See the message for details.
Message.UserResponse: Respond appropriately to the error message.

Message.MsgText: INSTALL_DISPLAY_BACKEND_CWSJO0052=CWSJO0052I: Using datasource backend ID: {0}
Message.Explanation: The script is declaring the detected backend ID. This identifies the type of database the SDO repository will be configured to use.
Message.UserResponse: No action is required.

Message.MsgText: INSTALL_SUCCESSFUL_CWSJO0023=CWSJO0023I: SDO repository installation completed successfully.
Message.Explanation: The installation has completed.
Message.UserResponse: No action is required.

Message.MsgText: NAME_NOT_FOUND_CWSJO0038=CWSJO0038E: Cannot find resource with name {0}
Message.Explanation: A resource with the given name is not stored in the repository.
Message.UserResponse: Use the correct name for the item for which you are searching, or add the item to the repository under this name.

Message.MsgText: INSTALL_BAD_CLUSTER_NAME_CWSJO0047=CWSJO0047E: Cannot find cluster {0}.
Message.Explanation: The specified cluster does not exist.
Message.UserResponse: Call the install script again with a valid cluster name.

Message.MsgText: RESERVED_NAME_CWSJO0007E=CWSJO0007E: Cannot edit the system resource: {0}.
Message.Explanation: Some resources in the repository are defined by the system. These resources cannot be edited.
Message.UserResponse: Choose a different name for user-defined resources.

Message.MsgText: VALUE_TOO_LONG_CWSJO0046=CWSJO0046E: The resource is too big for the system to store. The maximum permitted length of a resource is {0} bytes. The resource named "{1}" has a length of {2} bytes.
Message.Explanation: An attempt was made to register a resource that is longer than the underlying database will permit.
Message.UserResponse: Break the resource into smaller pieces to store in the repository.

Message.MsgText: INSTALL_CREATING_DATA_SOURCE_CWSJO0018=CWSJO0018I: Creating data source {0} under JDBC provider {1}.
Message.Explanation: The installer is creating a JDBC provider.
Message.UserResponse: No action is required.

Message.MsgText: INSTALL_DB_ALREDY_EXISTS_CWSJO0043=CWSJO0043E: Database directory already exists: {0}.
Message.Explanation: The installer cannot create a database in the named directory because the directory already exists.
Message.UserResponse: Delete the directory if it safe to do so, then run the installer again.

Message.MsgText: INSTALL_SAVING_CWSJO0022=CWSJO0022I: Saving configuration.
Message.Explanation: The configuration changes are being saved.
Message.UserResponse: No action is required.

Message.MsgText: INSTALL_CREATEDB_ON_ND_CWSJO0062=CWSJO0062E: -createDb cannot be used in a Network Deployment environment.
Message.Explanation: The "-createDb" option creates an embedded Derby database. Embedded Derby can only be used by the SDO repository on a stand-alone server.
Message.UserResponse: See the information center for instructions on how to install the SDO repository in a Network Deployment environment.

Message.MsgText: INSTALL_IJ_NOT_FOUND_CWSJO0040=CWSJO0040E: The ij command was not found. The expected location of ij is "{0}".
Message.Explanation: The install script cannot find the ij.bat or ij.sh command in the named directory. If this file does not exist the server installation is corrupted.
Message.UserResponse: Reinstall the application server to repair the installation.

Message.MsgText: OPTIMISTIC_UPDATE_FAILED_CWSJO0005E=CWSJO0005E: Cannot update resource: {0}. The update failed because the stored value was changed between the stream being created and the stream being closed.
Message.Explanation: An optimistic update strategy is used to write to the repository when using an OutputStream. The update failed because the stored value changed. The change might have been made by another thread.
Message.UserResponse: Check if the value should still be updated and, if so, repeat the command.

Message.MsgText: UNINSTALL_DATA_SOURCE_NOT_FOUND_CWSJO0026=CWSJO0026W: Cannot find data source {0}.
Message.Explanation: The data source created by the installer was not found.
Message.UserResponse: Locate the repository's data source and manually remove it.

Message.MsgText: MBEAN_REMOVE_FAIL_CWSJO0036=CWSJO0036E: Error while removing resource {0}: {1}
Message.Explanation: The resource cannot be removed. See the message for details.
Message.UserResponse: Respond appropriately to the error message.

Message.MsgText: INSTALL_DISPLAY_UPDATE_CWSJO0061=CWSJO0061I: Updating backend ID for application {0}.
Message.Explanation: The script is declaring that it is updating the backend ID of the SDO repository application.
Message.UserResponse: No action is required.

Message.MsgText: NULL_NAME_CWSJO0009=CWSJO0009E: The data access service registry cannot register a data access service factory under a null domain name.
Message.Explanation: An attempt was made to register a data access service factory using a null domain name.
Message.UserResponse: Ensure all calls to register data access service factories specify non-null domain names.

Message.MsgText: NULL_NAME_CWSJO0001=CWSJO0001E: The SDO repository cannot store a value under a null name.
Message.Explanation: An attempt was made to register a value in the repository using a null name.
Message.UserResponse: Ensure all calls to store data in the repository specify non-null names.

Message.MsgText: INSTALL_BACKEND_LIST_CWSJO0060=CWSJO0060I: Values marked with (**) cannot be used when the SDO repository is installed on one or more version 6 or version 6.1 servers.
Message.Explanation: The install script is displaying a list of valid parameters.
Message.UserResponse: No action is required.

Message.MsgText: INSTALL_APP_ALREDY_EXISTS_CWSJO0050=CWSJO0050I: Application already exists: {0}
Message.Explanation: The installation program endeds because the SDO repository application is already installed on the server.
Message.UserResponse: No action is required. The application is already installed.

Message.MsgText: UNINSTALL_DISPLAY_CLUSTER_CWSJO0053=CWSJO0053I: Uninstalling SDO repository on cluster {0}.
Message.Explanation: The script is declaring the cluster being used.
Message.UserResponse: No action is required.

Message.MsgText: NO_DATA_MEDIATOR_FOR_DOMAIN_CWSJO0008=CWSJO0008E: No data access service factory is registered for domain: {0}
Message.Explanation: The domain has not been registered to the system.
Message.UserResponse: Ensure the domain name is correct and that a data access service factory has been registered for the domain.

Message.MsgText: INSTALL_BACKEND_LIST_CWSJO0059=CWSJO0059I: The following values are valid for the BackendId parameter:{0} Values marked with (*) cannot be used when the SDO repository is installed on one or more version 6 servers.
Message.Explanation: The install script is displaying a list of valid parameters.
Message.UserResponse: No action is required.

Message.MsgText: MBEAN_EXPORT_FAIL_CWSJO0032=CWSJO0032E: Error exporting resource {0} to file {1}: {2}
Message.Explanation: The resource cannot be exported to the file. See the message for details.
Message.UserResponse: Respond appropriately to the error message.

Message.MsgText: INSTALL_INSTALLING_EJB_APP_CWSJO0021=CWSJO0021I: Installing SDO repository EJB application.
Message.Explanation: The installer is installing the application component of the SDO repository.
Message.UserResponse: No action is required.

Message.MsgText: INSTALL_BAD_SERVER_NAME_CWSJO0049=CWSJO0049E: Cannot find server {0} on node {1}.
Message.Explanation: The specified server does not exist.
Message.UserResponse: Call the script again with valid node and server names.

Message.MsgText: INSTALL_JDBC_PROVIDER_NOT_FOUND_CWSJO0012=CWSJO0012E: Installation failed. JDBC provider {0} does not exist.
Message.Explanation: To install the SDO repository, the installation program needs access to this JDBC provider.
Message.UserResponse: Restore the named JDBC provider or manually install the SDO repository.

Message.MsgText: UNABLE_TO_CREATE_REGISTRY_CWSJO0011=CWSJO0011E: A data access service registry instance cannot be created: exception {0}.
Message.Explanation: A data access service registry instance cannot be created because the sib.sdoConfig.jar file is missing or corrupted.
Message.UserResponse: If the problem persists, additional information might be available if you search for the message ID on the following Web sites: WebSphere Application Server Support page: http://www.ibm.com/software/webservers/appserv/was/support/ WebSphere Application Server for z/OS Support page: http://www.ibm.com/software/webservers/appserv/zos_os390/support/ .

Message.MsgText: TEMPORARY_CWSJO9999=CWSJO9999E: {0}
Message.Explanation: If the message does not give sufficient information, check previous messages for further help.
Message.UserResponse: See previous messages for further information.

Message.MsgText: UNINSTALL_DATA_SOURCE_REMOVED_CWSJO0025=CWSJO0025I: Successfully removed data source {0}.
Message.Explanation: The uninstaller has removed the data source used by the SDO repository.
Message.UserResponse: No action is required.

Message.MsgText: DATASOURCE_NOT_FOUND_CWSJO0057=CWSJO0057E: The SDO repository cannot find the data source: {0}
Message.Explanation: The SDO repository requires a data source and database to be configured for use.
Message.UserResponse: See the information center for details on configuring a data source for the SDO repository.

Message.MsgText: INSTALL_DISPLAY_SERVER_AND_NODE_CWSJO0016=CWSJO0016I: Installing SDO repository on node {0}, server {1}.
Message.Explanation: The script is declaring the server and node being used.
Message.UserResponse: No action is required.

Message.MsgText: STREAM_ALREADY_CLOSED_CWSJO0006E=CWSJO0006E: The stream is already closed.
Message.Explanation: A stream can only be closed once. This was probably caused by a client programming error.
Message.UserResponse: Only close the stream once.

Message.MsgText: INSTALL_CONNECTION_FACTORY_ALREADY_EXISTS_CWSJO0014=CWSJO0014E: CMP connection factory {0} already exists.
Message.Explanation: The installer cannot continue because the connection factory it will create already exists.
Message.UserResponse: If the SDO repository is already installed, do not install it again. Otherwise manually install the SDO repository to avoid naming conflicts with the existing configuration.

Message.MsgText: MBEAN_LIST_RESOURCES_FAIL_CWSJO0037=CWSJO0037E: Cannot list resources: {0}
Message.Explanation: There was an error while listing the resources. See the message for details.
Message.UserResponse: Respond appropriately to the error message.

Message.MsgText: INSTALL_DISPLAY_CLUSTER_CWSJO0048=CWSJO0048I: Installing SDO repository on cluster {0}.
Message.Explanation: The script is declaring the cluster being used.
Message.UserResponse: No action is required.

Message.MsgText: UNINSTALL_DISPLAY_SERVER_AND_NODE_CWSJO0044=CWSJO0044I: Uninstalling SDO repository on node {0}, server {1}.
Message.Explanation: The script is declaring the server and node being used.
Message.UserResponse: No action is required.

Message.MsgText: APP_NOT_FOUND_CWSJO0054=CWSJO0054E: The SDO repository application cannot be found.
Message.Explanation: The JNDI lookup for the SDO repository has failed.
Message.UserResponse: Install the SDO repository on the server being used, and ensure the repository has started.

Message.MsgText: INSTALL_CREATING_DB_CWSJO0042=CWSJO0042I: Creating Derby database. See log file for details at {0}.
Message.Explanation: The installer is creating a Derby database using the DDL file. The results of the database creation are saved to a log file.
Message.UserResponse: No action is required.

Message.MsgText: MBEAN_EXPORT_CWSJO0031=CWSJO0031I: Resource {0} exported to file {1}
Message.Explanation: The resource has been saved to disk.
Message.UserResponse: No action is required.

Message.MsgText: INSTALL_CREATING_CONNECTION_FACTORY_CWSJO0020=CWSJO0020I: Creating CMP connection factory for data source {0}.
Message.Explanation: The installer is creating a connection factory for the previously created data source.
Message.UserResponse: No action is required.

Message.MsgText: MBEAN_IMPORT_CWSJO0033=CWSJO0033I: Resource {0} imported from file {1}
Message.Explanation: The resource has been loaded from disk.
Message.UserResponse: No action is required.

Message.MsgText: INSTALL_CREATEDB_ON_ZOS_CWSJO0063=CWSJO0063E: -createDb cannot be used on a z/OS system.
Message.Explanation: The "-createDb" option creates an embedded Derby database. This database cannot be used on a z/OS system because embedded Derby can only be accessed by one process at a time, and Application Servers on z/OS contain multiple processes.
Message.UserResponse: See the information center for instructions on how to install the SDO repository on z/OS.
